{"word":"ἐπιστατέω","slug":"ἐπιστατέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπιστατέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐπιστάτης'><el>ἐπιστάτης</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be set over</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>: also <i>to stand by, to support, second</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to be in charge of, have the care of</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>at Athens, <i>to be</i> <el>Ἐπιστάτης</el> or <i>President</i> of the <el>βουλή</el> and <el>ἐκκλησία</el>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}